<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Getting Started with RSOLV</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #333;
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .logo {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
    }
    .logo img {
      max-width: 200px;
    }
    h1 {
      color: #2563EB;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    h2 {
      color: #2563EB;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #E5E7EB;
      padding-bottom: 10px;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }
    p {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .feature {
      background-color: #F9FAFB;
      border-left: 4px solid #2563EB;
      padding: 15px 20px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .feature h3 {
      margin-top: 0;
      color: #2563EB;
    }
    .cta {
      background-color: #2563EB;
      color: white;
      padding: 12px 24px;
      border-radius: 5px;
      display: inline-block;
      text-decoration: none;
      margin-top: 10px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .footer {
      margin-top: 40px;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: #6B7280;
      border-top: 1px solid #E5E7EB;
      padding-top: 20px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="logo">
    <img src="https://rsolv.dev/images/rsolv_logo_transparent.png" alt="RSOLV Logo">
  </div>

  <h1>Getting Started with RSOLV</h1>

  <p>Hi <%= @first_name %>,</p>

  <p>We hope you're enjoying RSOLV so far. Here's a quick overview of what you can do with our platform:</p>

  <div class="feature">
    <h3>üõ°Ô∏è Proactive Security Scanning</h3>
    <p>RSOLV continuously scans your repositories for vulnerabilities and automatically creates detailed security issues. We detect 180+ security patterns (and growing) across JavaScript, TypeScript, Python, Ruby, Java, and Go.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="feature">
    <h3>üöÄ Automated Vulnerability Detection & Fixes</h3>
    <p>RSOLV finds vulnerabilities before they become problems. When you're ready to fix them, just tag the issue with "rsolv:automate" and we'll generate a secure, well-documented pull request.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="feature">
    <h3>üí∞ Success-Based Billing</h3>
    <p>You only pay when security fixes are merged into your codebase. No seat licenses, no commitments - just $15 per successful fix after your 10 free fixes.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Quick Tips for Better Results</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Review security issues created by RSOLV's proactive scans</li>
    <li>Prioritize HIGH severity vulnerabilities first</li>
    <li>Use "rsolv:automate" label to generate fix PRs</li>
    <li>Each PR includes security impact analysis and tests</li>
    <li>Remember: You only need one API key (RSOLV_API_KEY)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>For detailed instructions, check out our documentation:</p>

  <a href={@docs_url} class="cta">View Documentation</a>

  <p>If you have any questions or need assistance, just reply to this email. We're here to help!</p>

  <p>Best,<br>The RSOLV Team</p>

  <div class="footer">
    <p>This email was sent to <%= @email %>. If you no longer wish to receive these emails, you can <a href={"https://rsolv.dev/unsubscribe?email=#{@email}"}>unsubscribe</a>.</p>
    <p>¬© 2025 RSOLV - Proactive Security Scanning & Automated Remediation. Pay Only for Fixes You Deploy.</p>
  </div>
</body>
</html>